cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper focuses on collaborative robotics and communication between robots and humans, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the interpretation of pointing actions, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed interpretive principles for robotic communication involve reasoning and decision-making, which are key components of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the principles involves analyzing animations, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
